Document: AnimatedTexture
Path: godot/classes/class_animatedtexture.rst
Summary: Defines the MAX_FRAMES constant and its usage limitations in AnimatedTexture.

MAX_FRAMES = 256. This is the maximum number of frames supported by AnimatedTexture. If you need more frames in your animation, use AnimationPlayer or AnimatedSprite2D. Note: This constant defines the upper limit for frame count in AnimatedTexture's internal frame management system. Exceeding this limit requires using alternative animation systems provided by Godot.
---CHUNK---
Document: AnimatedTexture  
Path: godot/classes/class_animatedtexture.rst  
Summary: Properties and methods for controlling animation playback, frame management, and speed in AnimatedTexture.  

current_frame (int): Sets the currently visible frame of the texture. Setting this frame while playing resets the current frame time, so the newly selected frame plays for its whole configured frame duration. Method: set_current_frame(value: int) → void. Method: get_current_frame() → int.  

frames (int, default: 1): Number of frames to use in the animation. While you can create the frames independently with set_frame_texture(), you need to set this value for the animation to take new frames into account. The maximum number of frames is MAX_FRAMES. Method: set_frames(value: int) → void. Method: get_frames() → int. Key Rule: The maximum number of frames is limited by MAX_FRAMES.  

one_shot (bool, default: false): If true, the animation will only play once and will not loop back to the first frame after reaching the end. Note: Reaching the end will not set pause to true. Method: set_one_shot(value: bool) → void. Method: get_one_shot() → bool.  

pause (bool, default: false): If true, the animation will pause where it currently is (i.e., at current_frame). The animation will continue from where it was paused when changing this property to false. Method: set_pause(value: bool) → void. Method: get_pause() → bool.  

speed_scale (float, default: 1.0): The animation speed is multiplied by this value. If set to a negative value, the animation is played in reverse. Method: set_speed_scale(value: float) → void. Method: get_speed_scale() → float.
---CHUNK---
Document: AnimatedTexture
Path: godot/classes/class_animatedtexture.rst
Summary: Methods for managing frame durations and textures in an AnimatedTexture.

Method: get_frame_duration(frame: int) → float. Returns the given frame's duration in seconds.

Method: get_frame_texture(frame: int) → Texture2D. Returns the given frame's Texture2D.

Method: set_frame_duration(frame: int, duration: float). Sets the duration of any given frame. The final duration is affected by the speed_scale property. Note: If set to 0, the frame is skipped during playback.

Method: set_frame_texture(frame: int, texture: Texture2D). Assigns a Texture2D to the given frame. Frame IDs start at 0, so the first frame has ID 0, and the last frame of the animation has ID frames - 1. You can define any number of textures up to MAX_FRAMES, but keep in mind that only frames from 0 to frames - 1 will be part of the animation.